This is a small program which looks at earthquakes from the USGS system.
It calculates the mean elevation & depth of a given section of earthquakes.

It also shows these graphically on a google map.

Build for the Practical Problem Solving module at Leeds University School of Computing

Requirements:
python3+, json, requests, sys, webbrowser, os

Usage: ./quakes.py <detail> <period>
(note! don't actually include the braces)

Values for detail: 2.5, 4.5, significant
Values for period: week, month

For more infomation please see:
http://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/feed/

 
